	add("belief", "{\"term\":\"belief\", \"etymology\":{\"influencers\":[], \"languages\":[\"old english (ca. 450-1100)\", \"English\", \"middle english (1100-1500)\"], \"text\":\"From Middle english (1100-1500) from Old english (ca. 450-1100) {{m|ang|lēafa}}, from Proto-germanic {{m|gem-pro|*laubô}}.\"}, \"definitions\":{\"list\":[{\"upperType\":\"NOUN\", \"text\":\"Mental acceptance of a claim as likely true\", \"priority\":1},{\"upperType\":\"NOUN\", \"text\":\"issue\u003d26|page\u003d48|magazine\u003d|title\u003d[http://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2013/nov/27/al-gore-veganism-eating-words-sceptical-meat-eating Why I\u0027m eating my words on veganism – passage\u003dThe \u0027\u0027belief\u0027\u0027 that there is no conflict between [livestock] farming and arable production also seems to be unfounded: by preventing the growth of trees and other deep vegetation in the hills and by compacting the soil, grazing animals cause a cycle of flash floods and drought, sporadically drowning good land downstream and reducing the supply of irrigation water\", \"priority\":2},{\"upperType\":\"NOUN\", \"text\":\"Faith or trust in the reality of something; often based upon one\u0027s own reasoning, trust in a claim, desire of actuality, and/or evidence considered\", \"priority\":3},{\"upperType\":\"NOUN\", \"text\":\"Something believed\", \"priority\":4},{\"upperType\":\"NOUN\", \"text\":\"The quality or state of believing\", \"priority\":5},{\"upperType\":\"NOUN\", \"text\":\"Religious faith\", \"priority\":6},{\"upperType\":\"NOUN\", \"text\":\"One\u0027s religious or moral convictions\", \"priority\":7}]}, \"synonyms\":{}}");

